Software

Lab Equipment Software

     * [http://grafana.org/]Grafana - Create a dashboard (online if you
       wish) that visualizes your experimental data.
     * [http://www.mmass.org/]mMass - Open-source software for mass
       spectrometers.
     * [http://www.stellarium.org/]Stellarium - Open-source planetarium
       software.

Modeling and Computation

     * [http://www.openscad.org/]OpenSCAD - 3D modeling software.
     * [https://cloud.sagemath.com/]SageMath - Open-source cloud-based
       computation (similar to MATLAB and Mathematica).
     * [https://www.gnu.org/software/octave/]GNU Octave - Free software
       numerical computation program, similar to MATLAB.
     * [http://dia-installer.de/]Dia - Open-source software for making
       diagrams.
     * [https://gephi.org/]Gephi - Open graph visualization platform.
     * [http://www.qgis.org/en/site/]QGIS - Open GIS software.
     * [http://www.realtimerendering.com/erich/minecraft/public/mineways/]
       Mineways - a tool for turning Minecraft model files into
       3D-printable .stl files
     * [https://www.epa.gov/cameo/aloha-software]ALOHA - A piece of
       software disributed by the EPA that models the threat zone for
       various types of chemical spill and explosion hazards.
     * [http://vegan.r-forge.r-project.org/]vegan - R package for
       statistical work in community ecology.

Publishing , Collaboration and Organization

     * [https://www.zotero.org/]Zotero - Open-source citation management
       software.
     * [http://tiddlywiki.com/]TiddlyWiki - Easily create your own wikis
       to organize information.
     * [http://evergreen-ils.org/]Evergreen ILS - Software for managing a
       library of books (and the loaning process).
     * [https://github.com/nasa/isle]ISLE - Open-source laboratory
       equipment inventory management system developed by NASA.
     * [http://www.ganttproject.biz/]GanttProject - Productivity tool for
       scheduling tasks and making Gantt charts.
     * [https://osf.io/]Open Science Framework - Open-source collaborative
       project manager for scientific research.
     * [http://calibre-ebook.com/]Calibre - eBook management software.
     * [https://www.librarything.com/]LibraryThing - an online platform
       for organizing your library.
     * [http://www.worldpece.org/]PECE - The Platform for Experimental and
       Collaborative Ethnography. This project provides an online platform
       for academic collaboration that helps keep track of complex
       attribution of credit. It is geared toward anthropologists but is
       expanding to become more broad.
     * [https://github.com/rapidpro/rapidpro]RapidPro - An open-source
       platform for building scalable applications that users can interact
       with via SMS.

Educational

     * [http://lightandmatter.com/]Light and Matter - Benjamin Crowell's
       free-to-download, cheap-to-buy open source physics textbooks.
     * [https://openstax.org/]OpenStax - Repository of open-licensed and
       collaboratively-edited textbooks on many basic subjects. You can
       download them as ebooks or order print copies.
     * [https://phet.colorado.edu/en/simulations/category/chemistry]PhET
       Simulations - CU Boulder interactive physics and chemistry
       simulations.
     * [http://library.uniteddiversity.coop/]United Diversity Co-op
       Library - A vast library of interesting textbooks and other
       resources in PDF form on such topics as permaculture, agriculture,
       economics, crafts and activism.
     * [https://microbewiki.kenyon.edu/index.php/MicrobeWiki]Microbe Wiki
       - A large student-edited multi-institutional wiki for microbiology.
     * [http://www.openculture.com/free_textbooks]OpenCulture Textbooks -
       The textbook section of a website dedicated to the open sharing of
       information.
     * [http://www.freetechbooks.com/categories]Free Tech Books - Free
       ebooks (mostly computer science and engineering).
     * [http://openwetware.org/wiki/Main_Page]OpenWetWare - A site that
       maintains a list of bio lab protocols as well as an electronic lab
       notebook for team use.

Tools and Equipment

Biology and Chemistry

     * [http://www.the-odin.com/]The ODIN - A distributor of affordable
       DIY biology equipment.
     * [https://www.bento.bio/]Bento Box - A low-cost PCR workstation from
       Bento Lab.
     * [http://opentrons.com/]OpenTrons - An open-source liquid-handling
       robot.
     * [http://openpcr.org/]OpenPCR - An open-source PCR thermocycler.
     * [http://www.yeastgenome.org/]SGD - Stanford University's
       Saccharomyces Genome Database.
     * [http://blast.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Blast.cgi]BLAST - Search tool for
       local alignment.
     * [http://iorodeo.com/]IORodeo - Sells a cheap open-source
       potentiostat, a colorimeter, and some other equipment.
     * [http://www.biosurplus.com/]BioSurplus - A supplier of used bio lab
       equipment.
     * [http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:1483]DremelFuge - A biology
       centrifuge that takes the form of a dremel attachment.
     * [http://www.biorxiv.org/content/early/2016/08/30/072207.full.pdf+ht
       ml]Paperfuge - An ultra-low cost, hand-powered centrifuge inspired
       by the mechanics of a whirligig toy.
     * [http://www.hivebio.org/projects/ministat-2/]Ministat - A DIY
       chemostat.
     * [https://nanoporetech.com/products/minion]MinION - An affordable,
       portable DNA/RNA sequencer.
     * [https://backyardbrains.com/products/spikerbox]SpikerBox - A
       bioamplifier for DIY neuroscience.

Environmental Science and Geology

     * [https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/angelrodriguez/raspberry-shak
       e-your-personal-seismograph]Raspberry Shake - A seismograph
       compatible with the Raspberry Pi.
     * [http://www.smokymtsci.com/]Smoky Mountain Scientific - Modular,
       Low cost, open-source instrumentation for environmental monitoring.
     * [https://www.lhc-ilc.physik.uni-bonn.de/research-groups/experimenta
       l-physics/prof.-k.-desch/research/airborne-wind-energy]AWEsome - An
       affordable airborne wind turbine prototype.

3D Printing and Fabrication

     * [https://www.thingiverse.com/]Thingiverse - A search engine for
       3D-printable models.
     * [https://ember.autodesk.com/]Ember - A comprehensively open-source
       DLP SLA 3D Printer project, powered by Autodesk.
     * [http://www.appropedia.org/3D_printable_science_equipment]3D
       Printable Science Equipment - A list of different 3d-printable
       science objects with models.
     * [https://preciousplastic.com/en/videos/build/extrusion/]Precious
       Plastic - Make your own 3D printer filament.

Electronics

     * [https://getchip.com/pages/chip]C.H.I.P - A $9 Linux computer.
     * [https://www.raspberrypi.org/products/pi-zero/]Raspberry Pi Zero -
       The cheapest, smallest Raspberry Pi ($5).
     * [https://www.particle.io/products/hardware/electron-cellular-dev-ki
       t?]Particle Electron - Raspberry Pi-like microcontroller for
       connecting the devices you make to the cellular network.
     * [https://www.sparkfun.com/]SparkFun - A company selling all sorts
       of electronics for DIY projects, including sensors.
     * [http://redpitaya.com/]Red Pitaya - Open-source tool with multiple
       signal processing functions, such as an oscilloscope, spectrum
       analyzer, signal generator, and more.
     * [http://podolabs.com/#buy]Podo - A stickable, hi-resolution
       Bluetooth camera.

Other

     * [http://opensourceecology.org/gvcs/gvcs-machine-index/]Global
       Village Construction Set - Open-source farm equipment and other
       civilization-building tools.
     * [https://farmingconcrete.org/toolkit/]Farming Concrete Data
       Collection Toolkit - "Methods for measuring the outcomes and
       impacts of community gardens and urban farms."
     * [http://www.instructables.com/contest/buildmylab/]Build My Lab
       Contest - A competition to create instructables for DIY lab
       equipment.
     * [http://hackteria.org/wiki/Generic_Lab_Equipment]Generic Lab
       Equipment - Wiki with instructions on building DIY lab equipment.

Publishing and Doing Research

     * [http://theoryandpractice.citizenscienceassociation.org/]Citizen
       Science: Theory and Practice - An open-access, peer-reviewed
       journal dedicated to discussion about methods in citizen science.
     * [https://www.reddit.com/r/scholar]Scholar Subreddit - A great place
       to request help getting access to scientific papers that are beyond
       paywalls.
     * [http://libgen.io/]LibGen - An online tool for gaining access to
       scientific articles that are normally beyond paywalls.
     * [https://sci-hub.tw/]SciHub - Another site for gaining access to
       science papers that are normally behind paywalls.
     * [https://plos.org/]Public Library of Science (PLOS) - Nonprofit
       organization that publishes open-access journals and also advocates
       for openness and tranparency in science.
     * [http://arxiv.org/]arXiv - A Cornell-supported site for sharing and
       discussing early drafts of scientific papers (mostly physics and
       math).
     * [https://doaj.org/]Directory of Open Access Journals - Over 9000
       journals listed.
     * [https://investigativedashboard.org/]Investigative Dashboard - A
       tool for researchers, especially journalists, to share documents
       and findings.

Literature

Citizen Science Theory

     * [http://estsjournal.org/article/view/99/58]Citizen Science: Probing
       the Virtues and Contexts of Participatory Research
     * [https://www.academia.edu/7622292/Buckets_of_Resistance_Standards_a
       nd_the_Effectiveness_of_Citizen_Science?auto=download]Buckets of
       Resistance: Standards and the Effectiveness of Citizen Science
     * [http://davidjhess.net/uploads/3/4/8/1/34811322/socinquiry.2009.dra
       ft.pdf]The Potentials and Limitations of Civil Society Research:
       Getting Undone Science Done
     * [https://peer.asee.org/citizen-engineering-disrupting-expertise-in-
       classroom-and-community]Citizen Engineering: Disrupting Expertise
       in Classroom and Community - A paper introducing the concept of
       "citizen engineering" as a companion to citizen science
     * [https://www.researchgate.net/publication/263120833_Institutions_fo
       r_Civic_Technoscience_How_Critical_Making_is_Transforming_Environme
       ntal_Research]Institutions for Civic Technoscience: How Critical
       Making is Transforming Environmental Research
     * [http://www.jstor.org/stable/pdf/27896218.pdf]Citizen Science as an
       Ecological Research Tool: Challenges and Benefits
     * [http://online.liebertpub.com/doi/10.1089/ees.2016.0223]Academic
       Research in the 21st Century: Maintaining Scientific Integrity in a
       Climate of Perverse Incentives and Hypercompetition
     * [http://www.its.caltech.edu/%7Ebi/labinger/nontechpdfs/7sciencewars
       .pdf]The Science Wars and the Future of the American Academic
       Profession - Caltech chemistry professor Jay A. Labinger's paper
       about the need for scientists to engage with critical science
       studies scholars.
     * [http://science-for-the-people.org/]Science for the People - A late
       1960s/early 1970s radical science movement whose literature has
       been organized on a website by UMass Amherst.
     * [https://www.fromthesquare.org/march-science-abolitionist-science/#
       .WPpQv2nyuUl]From the March for Science to an Abolitionist Science
       - An article that offers several historical and current critiques
       of science that propose alternative ways of doing scientific work.
     * [http://www.wholeearth.com/index.php]Whole Earth Catalog - A site
       that contains the remnants of a famous late 1960s and early 1970s
       maker/ecology magazine.

Citizen Science Practice

     * [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1651267/pdf/amjph0064
       7-0022.pdf]Lead Concentrations in Inner-City Soils As a Factor in
       the Child Lead Problem - A 1983 pharmacology paper detailing a
       low-cost, low-tech method of doing soil heavy metal testing.
     * [https://civiclaboratory.nl/2017/03/31/how-to-run-a-feminist-scienc
       e-lab-meeting/]How to Run a Feminist Science Lab Meeting - A guide
       by the Civic Laboratory in St. John's, Newfoundland
     * [http://www.pharmtech.com/spectrophotometric-determination-lead]Spe
       ctrophotometric Determination of Lead - Another simple DIY lead
       testing procedure.
     * [https://news.nationalgeographic.com/2017/12/animals-grieving-pecca
       ries-death-mourning/]First-Ever Video May Show Pig-Like Animals
       Mourning Their Dead - An example of an important scientific
       discovery being made by someone who was not an institutional
       academic (an 8-year-old boy). The boy received lead author credit
       in a scientific paper.

Citizen Science Spaces and Projects

Genetics/Biohacking

     * [http://genspace.org/]Genspace - One of the oldest and most
       successful DIY Bio labs, located in Brooklyn, NYC.
     * [http://biocurious.org/]BioCurious - The first biohacking space in
       the world, located in Sunnyvale, CA
     * [http://hivebio.org/]HiveBio - Seattle community bio lab.
     * [http://www.syntechbio.com/]SynthTechBio Network - Latin American
       biohackers' network.
     * [https://fourthievesvinegar.org/]Four Thieves Vinegar Collective -
       A group working on DIY pharma-hacking projects, such as a $30
       alternative to $600 epi-pens.

Environment

     * [http://www.communityscience.org/]The Community Science Initiative
       - A nonprofit water testing and environmental data organization in
       Ithaca, NY.
     * [http://ellieirons.com/projects/sanctuary/]Sanctuary for Weedy
       Species - A Brooklyn-based urban ecology project.
     * [https://listening.coweeta.uga.edu/]Coweeta Listening Project -
       Southern Appalachian project combining ecological research with
       civic action.
     * [https://radixcenter.org/]The Radix Center - Community-based urban
       sustainability / agriculture education center in Albany, NY.
     * [http://www.labucketbrigade.org/]The Bucket Brigade - A Norco, LA -
       based citizen science group fighting for environmental justice.
     * [http://blog.safecast.org/]Safecast - An online citizen science
       project collecting and visualizing radioactivity data across the
       globe.
     * [https://rfcx.org/]Rainforest Connection - Project sing old
       smartphones as sensors to combat illegal logging.

Other

     * [http://www.thecitizensciencelab.org/]The Citizen Science Lab - A
       community science lab based in Pittsburgh, PA.
     * [http://www.biobus.org/]BioBus - A mobile science education lab.
     * [http://www.hillsboro-oregon.gov/departments/library/explore-the-co
       llections/library-of-things]Hillsboro Library of Things - A library
       for physical objects based in Hillsboro, OR. Includes some science
       and tech supplies.
     * [http://fabfoundation.org/]Fab Foundation - an organization that
       facilitaties a network of digital fabrication "Fab Labs"
     * [http://farmhack.org/tools]Farm Hack - A project for producing open
       farm tools.

Art and Science Spaces

   Community-driven science labs tend to operate differently from
   conventional labs. Their member-led and curiosity-driven approach often
   produces work that breaks down conventional disciplines, such as
   bio-art. This section is for listing spaces that may or may not be
   conventional makerspaces but capture this spirit of
   interdisciplinarity.
     * [https://www.buffalo.edu/genomeenvironmentmicrobiome/coalesce.html]
       Coalesce: Center for Biological Arts - A bioart studio-lab at SUNY
       Buffalo.
     * [http://www.media.mit.edu/]MIT Media Lab - An interdisciplinary
       art, science and technology research center that is part of the
       Massachusetts Institute of Technology.
     * [http://www.interspecifics.cc/]Interspecifics - A Mexico City-based
       collective working on projects at the intersection of art and
       science, especially related to biologically-generated sound.
     * [http://csi.asu.edu/]Center for Science and the Imagination - A
       collaboration between artists and scientists at Arizona State
       University.
     * [http://stemtosteam.org/]STEM to STEAM - An initiative out of Rhode
       Island School of Design to bring more art and design into STEM
       education.
     * [https://waag.org/en/]The Waag Society - An institute for
       collaborative art, science and technology based in the Netherlands.

Funding and Support

Financial Resources

     * [https://experiment.com/]Experiment.com - A science crowdfunding
       platform.
     * [http://www.awesomefoundation.org/]The Awesome Foundation - A
       nonprofit that funds awesome projects with microgrants $1000 at a
       time.
     * [https://www.endeavorist.org/#!/]Endeavorist - A "curiosity
       network" for science and technology that combines a social network
       with crowdfunding.
     * [http://www.herbsociety.org/support/grants-scholarships/grant-detai
       ls.html]Herb Society of America - Offers some grants that are
       compatible with small, non-institutional research projects.
     * [https://seedinglabs.org/]Seeding Labs - Equipment and funding for
       labs in developing countries.
     * [https://www.epa.gov/education/environmental-education-ee-grants]EP
       A Environmental Education Grants - Grants available for small
       community organizations.

Other Types of Support

     * [https://diybio.org/]DIYbio.org - An online community for DIY
       biologists.
     * [http://collabfinder.com/]CollabFinder - A place to find
       collaborators for your project.
     * [http://openlab-blueprint.org/]OpenLab-Blueprint - Informational
       resources for upstart DIY science labs, put together by members of
       Genspace.
     * [http://scistarter.com/finder]SciStarter - A search engine for
       finding citizen science projects to participate in.
     * [https://crowdsourcing-toolkit.sites.usa.gov/]Federal Crowdsourcing
       and Citizen Science Toolkit - Maintained by the US government.
     * [https://publiclab.org/]Public Lab - A DIY environmental science
       network.
     * [http://bio.academany.org/2015/labs/luzern/final_project.html]Welco
       me to How To Grow (almost) Anything in GaudiLabs - Switzerland - A
       guide to setting up a basic microbiology lab.

Conferences and Events

     * [http://www.innovative-citizen.de/]Innovative Citizen - An annual
       citizen science festival in the Ruhr area, Germany, with an
       emphasis on organic fabrication, bio-hacking, mobile agriculture,
       and sustainability in urban ecosystems.
     * [http://igem.org/Main_Page]iGEM - Student synthetic biology
       competition with connections to many DIY bio labs.
     * [http://www.biofabricate.co/]Biofabricate - A design-focused annual
       conference that focuses on biotechnology-affiliated design,
       materials, and techniques.
     * [http://biodesignchallenge.org/]Biodesign Challenge - Student
       design competition that concentrates on envisioning the future
       application of biotechnology.

Other Resources

     * [http://www.appropedia.org/Category:MOST]MOST - The Pearce Research
       Group at Michigan Tech in Open Sustainability Technology.
     * [http://www.osgeo.org/]OSGeo - The Open Source Geospatial
       Foundation, which offers a lot of open tools for working with GIS
       data.
     * [http://www.appropedia.org/Open_source_engineering_software#Softwar
       e_Listing]Open source engineering software - A large list
       maintained on Appropedia.
     * [http://www.oshwa.org/]The Open Source Hardware Association - A
       resource for all things open hardware, including designs and legal
       considerations.
     * [http://biocanvas.net/]Biocanvas - A collection of biological
       images as art.
     * [https://www.powercube.net/]The Powercube - Some literature and
       workshops by community organizers for understanding power and
       mobilizing.

Questions and Knowledge Gaps

     * Ethics in research are often overseen by federal agencies or
       institutional review boards (IRBs). Is there a bottom-up,
       citizen-driven alternative to this?

How do I contribute to this list?

   Have an idea of a tool that should be on this list? Here's how you can
   add it:
     * Familiar with GitHub? Send a pull request with your suggestions.
       Please also see the
       [https://github.com/dylanrees/toolsforcitizenscience/blob/master/co
       ntributing.md]contribution guidelines.
     * Not familiar with GitHub? You can leave a comment on this page by
       clicking on the Issues tab on the right and adding a New Issue
       (that's just like a comment). You'll need to create a GitHub
       account first.

